            <div class="content">
                <h3>
                    1.	&nbsp; &nbsp; PURPOSE   :
                </h3>
                <p style="margin-left:50px;">
                    The purpose of this procedure is
                    to describe the methodology for planning and implementing
                    internal audit to verify whether quality management system
                    requirements and related results are comply with planned arrangements
                    and to determine the effectively implementation & maintenance of the quality
                    management system.
                </p>
                <h3>
                    2.	&nbsp; &nbsp; SCOPE   :
                </h3>
                <p style="margin-left:50px;">
                    Applicable to all areas covered under the quality management system.
                </p>
                <h3>
                    3.	&nbsp; &nbsp; RESPONSIBILITY    :
                </h3>
                <p style="margin-left:50px;">
                    MR, auditors and auditee are responsible to implement and maintain this procedure.
                </p>
                <h3>
                    4.	&nbsp; &nbsp; PURPOSE   :
                </h3>
                <h5 style="margin-left:50px;">
                    4.1&nbsp; &nbsp;	DEFINITION &nbsp;:
                </h5>
                <ol style="list-style:lower-alpha;margin-left:100px;">
                    <li><span class="term">&nbsp;Auditor</span> <span class="separator">:</span> The person who audits the department.</li>
                    <li><span class="term">&nbsp;Auditee</span> <span class="separator">:</span> The persons being audited.</li>
                    <li><span class="term">&nbsp;Compliance</span> <span class="separator">:</span> The observed results are as per the specified requirements.</li>
                    <li><span class="term">&nbsp;Non-conformity</span> <span class="separator">:</span> The observed results are not as per the specified requirements.</li>
                </ol>
                <h5 style="margin-left:50px;">
                    4.2	&nbsp; &nbsp;AUDITOR &nbsp;:
                </h5>
                <strong style="margin-left:90px;">4.2.1</strong>
                <p style="margin-left:100px;">

                    MR shall maintain the list of trained auditors in doc. no. DMR07. MR shall arrange to conduct the internal auditors training.
                    After completion of training programme, test shall be carried out. After qualifying the test, auditor shall be considered as a trained auditor.
                    Incase decided by the management, internal audit service shall be purchased from the outside agency.
                </p>
                <h5 style="margin-left:50px;">
                    4.3	INTERNAL &nbsp; AUDIT &nbsp; PLAN &nbsp;:
                </h5>
                <strong style="margin-left:90px;">4.3.1</strong>
                <p style="margin-left:100px;">

                    Internal audit shall be conducted once in a year and MR shall prepare the internal audit plan in doc. no. DMR08.

                </p><strong style="margin-left:90px;">4.3.2</strong>
                <p style="margin-left:100px;">
                    Based on the internal audit plan, MR shall prepare the internal audit schedule in form no. F MR 07, which includes
                    the Scope of Audit, Name of the auditor, Name of the auditee, Department to be audited and Date & time.
                </p>
                <strong style="margin-left:90px;">4.3.3</strong>
                <p style="margin-left:100px;">
                    During preparation of audit programme MR shall ensures that auditors are independent of those activities having
                    direct responsibility for the activity being audited. MR shall inform to all auditors and Audi tee’s in advance.

                </p>
                <strong style="margin-left:90px;">4.3.4</strong>
                <p style="margin-left:100px;">

                    In case any auditor / auditee can not able to present during the audit, the concerned person shall inform to
                    MR and accordingly MR shall decide the necessary action.
                </p>
