            <div class="content">

                <h5 style="margin-left:50px;">
                    4.4&nbsp; &nbsp;	AUDIT &nbsp; PROCESS &nbsp; :
                </h5>

                <strong style="margin-left:90px;">4.4.1</strong>
                <p style="margin-left:100px;">

                    Auditor shall carry out internal audit as per the audit schedule and verify whether quality management system and related results comply with planned arrangements.
                </p>
                <strong style="margin-left:90px;">4.4.2</strong>
                <p style="margin-left:100px;">

                    Internal audit shall be conducted once in a year and MR shall prepare the internal audit plan in doc. no. DMR08.

                </p><strong style="margin-left:90px;">4.4.2</strong>
                <p style="margin-left:100px;">
                    Auditor shall record the compliance or observations found during the audit.
                </p>
                <strong style="margin-left:90px;">4.4.3</strong>
                <p style="margin-left:100px;">
                    Auditee shall identify the root cause and decide the corrective action plan along
                    with target date in audit NC report, form no. FMR08.
                </p>
                <strong style="margin-left:90px;">4.4.4</strong>
                <p style="margin-left:100px;">

                    After deciding the action, auditor shall submit the copy and observations to MR.
                </p>
                <strong style="margin-left:90px;">4.4.5</strong>
                <p style="margin-left:100px;">

                    MR shall review the same.
                </p>
                <h5 style="margin-left:50px;">
                    4.5&nbsp; &nbsp; FOLLOW &nbsp;UP &nbsp; AUDITS &nbsp; & &nbsp;EFFECTIVENESS &nbsp; :
                </h5>
                <strong style="margin-left:90px;">4.5.1</strong>
                <p style="margin-left:100px;">
                    As per the target date, MR/auditor shall verify the corrective action taken
                    by the auditee and collect the first copy. MR shall review the same and signed
                    it as a formal closing non-conformity.
                </p>
                <strong style="margin-left:90px;">4.5.2</strong>
                <p style="margin-left:100px;">
                    After closing the non-conformity, MR shall hand over second copy to auditee as a
                    closing of non-conformity and keep first copy with him as a record.
                </p>
                <strong style="margin-left:90px;">4.5.3</strong>
                <p style="margin-left:100px;">
                    MR shall review the effectiveness of corrective action taken during the next round
                    of internal audit and record shall be maintained in audit non-conformity report form no. F MR 08.
                </p>
                <strong style="margin-left:90px;">4.5.4</strong>
                <p style="margin-left:100px;">
                    MR shall review the effectiveness of corrective action taken during the next round
                    of internal audit and record shall be maintained in audit non-conformity report form no. F MR 08.
                </p>
                <strong style="margin-left:90px;">4.5.5</strong>
                <p style="margin-left:100px;">
                    MR shall prepare the Internal Audit NC summary report form no. of each round of Internal Audits.
                </p>
